preambule.al:
Having regard to the Convention for the establishment of
a European Space Agency of 30 May 1975, and in particular to its
Article VI and its Annex I on Privileges and Immunities;

li.al:
“Convention”
means the Convention for the establishment of a European Space Agency
of 30 May 1975;

“the
Agency” means the European Space
Agency;

“ESTEC” means
the European Space Research Technology Centre of the Agency located in
the Netherlands;

“Government” means the
Government of the
Netherlands;

“Vienna
Convention” means the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations
of 18 April 1961;

excise duties
(accijnzen) on
goods;

insurance
tax
(assurantiebelasting);

import
taxes and duties
(invoerrechten);

energy
tax
(energiebelasting);

ground
water tax
(grondwaterbelasting);

the
spouse or registered partner of a staff
member;

children of a staff member,
of his spouse or of his registered partner who are under the age of
18;

representatives
of Member States, as defined in Article XIV of Annex 1 of the
Convention;

staff members and members
of their family forming part of their
household;

experts and members of
their family forming part of their
household;
